        "label": "Keystone user email/password",
        "setup": "Create a user in your Keystone app’s auth list during first run or via your app’s user management flow. Keystone’s auth system expects an identity field such as `email` and a secret `password` field, configured with `createAuth()` from `@keystone-6/auth`. The docs show the first-user flow in the starter app and the `authenticateUserWithPassword` GraphQL mutation for signing in. See [Authentication and Access Control](https://keystonejs.com/docs/guides/auth-and-access-control) and [Authentication](https://keystonejs.com/docs/config/auth)."
      },
      "keystone_session_cookie_secret": {
        "type": "two_step",
        "label": "Keystone session secret / session cookie configuration",
        "setup": "Configure the Keystone session strategy in your app, typically with `statelessSessions()` or `storedSessions()` from `@keystone-6/core/session`. Provide a strong `secret` (at least 32 characters) and related cookie settings such as `path`, `domain`, `sameSite`, and `secure`. See [Session](https://keystonejs.com/docs/config/session)."
      }
